cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a deep learning model for air quality forecasting, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks and long short-term memory networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to deep learning and neural networks. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The use of neural networks also falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of spatial-temporal correlation features, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the use of time series data, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
